This might be the most humbling day in my glass collecting experience. My terrible pics don’t do this chip any justice. This icy @roseroadskojima millie chip is the exact image that inspired me to begin collecting glass some 7 years ago. I’ve been fortunate to own a lot of glass in my life, but I have to say this is right up there as one of my most treasured pieces of art. Thank you so much @mainglassman for allowing me to finally end my search for this image. It’s even more incredible in person 👊🏼 #roseroads #roseroadskojima #myholygrail #collectorschip #nfse #headyart #glassart

Here’s another piece I made in my class at Penland with @carmenlozar. Carmen presented us with this cobalt blue glass base as a jumping board for any idea we could think of. I immediately envision a little figure diving. I’m so fortunate I went with my instinct- I say this very rarely, but it came out exactly how I pictured and I couldn’t be any happier with the outcome. I really love how simple, yet expressive it is. And with this one idea came a million more! Thanks for looking ✨

Available- All cold worked, hand carved pendys for sale. Desperately need to move some glass, not making it here. Literally just trying to feed my family with these sales.
